status_message: Today's global financial crisis has spawned massive dislocations of many new and surprising types. The current economic downturn, unlike others in the past, is hurting not just the already-poor but also people who were considered safe and well off. Once mighty banks have been brought low or destroyed. And millions of people who were living the American dream as homeowners are heading for the street. Literally. The images of homelessness sunken-cheeked men railing against imaginary voices now include the specter of the family next door former homeowners and the recently unemployed. These once middle-class folks now have been tossed into desperation by the international credit crunch.
link_name: Changing Face of Homelessness
